# Edge response headers for the deployed app (Cloudflare Workers static assets
# serve this file — copied verbatim from public/ into the build root). This is
# the AUTHORITATIVE Content-Security-Policy for staging/production.
#
# A second, ALWAYS-ON <meta> CSP floor is injected by src/main.jsx (dev AND
# prod) so the app is never left with zero CSP if this header isn't served. The
# meta floor mirrors the policy below MINUS the header-only directives
# (frame-ancestors + X-Frame-Options/X-Content-Type-Options/Referrer-Policy).
# KEEP THE TWO IN SYNC — edit both when a directive changes. The browser
# enforces the intersection, so the header's frame-ancestors still applies.
#
# Native (Capacitor) loads the hosted origin as a live web view, so it inherits
# this policy too. `frame-ancestors 'none'` is a top-level page constraint and
# does not affect the WKWebView/WebView shell (it is not an iframe embed).
#
# Directive notes:
#   default-src 'self'      lock everything down; widen per-type below
#   object-src 'none'       no <object>/<embed>/<applet> (task requirement)
#   base-uri 'self'         block <base> tag base-URL hijacking (task req.)
#   frame-ancestors 'none'  clickjacking protection — cannot be set via <meta>,
#                           which is exactly why the real header is required
#   script-src 'self'       bundled JS only; no inline/eval (no 'unsafe-inline')
#   style-src 'unsafe-inline' react-bootstrap + inline style attrs need it
#   connect-src https:      the DataManager API + Cognito token endpoint vary by
#                           environment and the app derives them from config, so
#                           any https origin is permitted (plus SSE + media)
#   img-src data: blob: https:  signed S3 media + data/blob previews
#   font-src 'self'         DM Sans is self-hosted via @fontsource (bundled)
# Cache policy (2026-07-23, self-update fix): the WebView shells cache
# aggressively, so a cold start could boot a STALE bundle. HTML (and anything
# unhashed) must revalidate every load; hashed /assets/* are immutable by
# construction so they cache forever; /version.json is the update probe and
# must never be cached anywhere. Later rules override earlier ones per header.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob: https:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https:
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  Cache-Control: no-cache

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/version.json
  Cache-Control: no-store
